HEADWORD: Provenience
<hw>Pro*ve"ni*ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>proveniens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p.pr. of <ets>provenire</ets>
to come forth; <ets>pro</ets> forth + <ets>venire</ets> to come.]</ety>
<def>Origin; source; place where found or produced; provenance; -- used
esp. in the fine arts and in arch⟦ae⟧ology; <as>as, the
<ex>provenience</ex> of a patera</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provenient</ent>⟦br⟧
